==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bufonite
<hw>Bu"fon*ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>bufo</ets> toad: cf. F. <ets>bufonite</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An old name for a fossil consisting of the
petrified teeth and palatal bones of fishes belonging to the family of
Pycnodonts (thick teeth), whose remains occur in the o⟦oum⟧lite and
chalk formations; toadstone; -- so named from a notion that it was
originally formed in the head of a toad.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

